<br>
Well that was the old party line for a loooooong time.  Then came the revelation from Verant that stats really mean very little beyond a certain point.  The law of diminishing returns in effect.<br>
<br>
AC is King.<br>
<br>
This is the latest party line.  For most melee classes I would agree.  But Bards are not a melee class, we are a support class.  Personally I want the most AC I can get without sacrificing DEX or CHR.  The Kunark armor is another choice.  But that is all it is a choice.  Some of the pieces have useful effects, but the only pieces I envision myself actually wearing full time are the Greaves and the BP.  There will be twinks in nearly full SS in no time flat, mark my words.  I want to stand out.  I will wear Imbrued.  I will honor the commitment it takes to get the Greaves and BP by wearing them full-time to honor the raid group that helped me attain them (eventually  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   ), but the rest will be in my Tinkers Bag and equipped only when I want the effect.<br>
<br>
Resists are King?<br>
<br>
I think this line of thinking will catch on in the near future.  More and more &quot;Boss MOB's&quot; will require resistance gear to combat effectively.<br>
<br>
I think Verant has given us a choice.  Imbrued is a good balanced set of armor.  Good AC, nice stat bonuses, mediocre resists.  Singing Steel is a great AC armor, no resists to speak of, low stat bonuses.  Velious armor?  Who can say.  Personally I think it will tend to do for resistances what Singing Steel did for AC.<br>
<br>
Only time will tell. <p><font size=2 face="Tempus Sans ITC, Verdana, Helvetica">
