<br>
Tanks:  Need high AC, high STR, high STA<br>
Wizards:  High INT<br>
Clerics/Druids/Shaman:  High Wisdom<br>
Monks/Rogues:  High AGI<br>
Enchanters:  High CHA, high INT<br>
<br>
Since bards are the jack of all trades and the master of none, we dont have any single area where we need to focus.  Bards tend to use a liitle bit of everything.<br>
<br>
STR:  For melee combat and carrying capacity (all those damn instruments)<br>
STA:  For increased HPS and stamina<br>
DEX:  For melee combat and Rogue skills<br>
AGI:  For defense in melee combat<br>
INT:  For mana and trade skills<br>
WIS:  For increased effectiveness in trade skills<br>
CHA:  For our Charm/Fear/Mes type songs<br>
AC:  Since we do get beat on and we have fewer defensive skills and fewer HPs<br>
HPS:  Always helps to have those extra few<br>
<br>
And everyone could use higher resists.<br>
<br>
So many other classes can abandon one stat or the other to improve their primary.  Since bards rely on all of them, they cant really focus on one too much over another.  This means we are very generalized, which is the very spirit of the Bard.<br>
<br>
And never forget fashion.  Bards more then any other class concern themselves with how they look.  We are travellers and entertainers.  You should always look your best!<br>
<br>
I think the AC from SS is worth the change from Imbrued and stats.  With such low caps in dodge, parry, and riposte, you need to keep your AC high (hint:  Bards are a Plate wearing class for a reason).  There are enough items in the game (necklaces, cloaks, helms, belts, rings, weapons etc...) to offest the drop in stats.<br>
<br>
